n","meanings":["English: variant of   Button   1 and 2.","Norwegian: habitational name from any of various farms named Botn, Botten, or Botnen, from Old Norse <i>botn</i> ‘small valley, valley end’. Compare   Botner  ."]},{"name":"Booten","meanings":["English: variant of   Button  . Compare   Booton  .","In some cases possibly also Dutch and North German: patronymic from a short form of the ancient Germanic personal name   Bodo  . This surname is rare in the Netherlands and Germany."]},{"name":"Butner","meanings":["English (Durham): occupational name of Norman origin from Old French <i>botonier</i> ‘button maker’, from <i>bo(u)ton</i> ‘knob, lump’, specialized to mean ‘button’.","In some cases also German (mainly <b>Bütner</b>): very rare variant of <b>Büttner</b> (see   Buettner  ) and, in North America, probably also an altered form of this."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir John de Button was born about 1183, in Bitton, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom. He married Lady Hawise Furneaux in 1214, in Bitton, Gloucestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters."},"et":{"about 1183–":"umbes 1183–Surnud","1194–Female":"1194–Surnud","1215–Male":"1215–Surnud","1217–Female":"1217–Surnud","1224–Female":"1224–Surnud","1183–Male":"1183–Surnud","about 1183":"umbes 1183","1217":"1217","1215":"1215","1214":"1214","about 1217":"umbes 1217","1224":"1224","about 1224":"umbes 1224","1183":"1183","1194":"1194","Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bitton, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Bitton, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bitton, Gloucestershire, England":"Bitton, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1183–":"noin 1183–Kuollut","1194–Female":"1194–Kuollut","1215–Male":"1215–Kuollut","1217–Female":"1217–Kuollut","1224–Female":